"hands down the best schmalz brew I've had, its fantastic, and a pleasant surprise for me. jet black in color, really really dark, with over an inch of tannish head, frothy and unfading. it has a nose nowhere near as hoppy as i expected, and its got more pine resin than bitterness to it, which is also a welcomed surprise. the malt is dominant though, dark like a stout, but with a lightness to the feel by both a softer body and upbeat carbonation. there is a nice char coffee bitterness on the front end, and the christmas tree type hops on the finish, with only moderate bitterness. its clean finishing for its size, i think the grain bill is really awesome on it, 7 malts, they don't tell you which, but its done right. i have yet to really be impressed with anything from these guys, but this to me is an overwhelming success, and one of the best black india pale ales in recent memory for me. its super dark and chalky textured, and its not over hopped. rock solid."
